    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Leonhard von Vels (Prague, 25 July 1544)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">Schlacher, an illustrious Banská Štiavnica citizen,
                            laments that his 16-year-old stepson, who had gone to take care of some
                            affairs, was caught by Dubowsky’s servitors. They thought they would
                            find silver on him, although of course there was none on him, and he has
                            been in captivity ever since. Schlacher asked Oláh to talk to Vels and
                            make sure the youngster is released; Dubowsky should receive the same
                            order from the King.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Generose et Magnifice Domine Observandisime, salutem et obsequiorum
                    commendationem!</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Lamentatur is circumspectus <persName>Quirinus
                        Schlaher</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.1">Quirin Schlacher or
                        Schlachter was a <hi rend="italic">Waldbürger</hi> in Banská Štiavnica and
                        later became Mayor of the city. In 1544, he launched a foundation for
                        Lutherans students in Wrocław, see <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Meier–Piirainen–Wegera</hi> 2009, 598; <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Scheible</hi> 1996, 276; and <hi rend="smallcap">Probszt</hi> 1958,
                        139.</note> civis Scemniciensis, qualiter superioribus temporibus quendam
                    adolescentem annorum nactum sedecim, privignum suum negotiorum suorum quorundam
                    causa <placeName>Wratislaviam</placeName> proficiscentem servitores domini
                        <persName>Ioannis Dobowczky</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.2"
                        >Probably Johannes Dubowsky. We only know him from a document from the year
                        1535 (Archiv of Banksá Bystrica), see <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Meier–Piirainen–Wegera</hi> 2009, 231.</note> ob suspicionem quandam
                    eductionis argenti, cum ne minimum quidem argenti granum apud eundem repertum
                    fuisset, in via publica sociis ipsius interemptis cepissent et in hunc usque
                    diem in dura captivitate idem dominus <persName>Doboczky</persName> eum teneret.
                    Unde rogavit me idem <persName>Quirinus</persName>, ut pro eodem adolescente
                    Dominationem Vestram Magnificam interpellarem, cui non potui meam operam
                    denegare. Rogo itaque Dominationem Vestram Magnificam, velit et aequitatis et in
                    mei gratiam cum domino <persName>Ioanne Doboczky</persName> agere, ut praefatum
                    adolescentem ex captivitate liberum dimittere, et dimitti facere velit; sicuti
                    etiam idem dominus <persName>Ioannes Doboczky</persName> ex litteris regiae
                    maiestatis, domini nostri clementissimi, hac in re ad eum datis id in commissis
                    et mandatis <choice>
                        <orig>habet</orig>
                        <supplied>habeat</supplied>
                    </choice>. Dominationem Vestram Magnificam feliciter valere opto.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Datum <placeName>Pragae</placeName> vigesimaquinta Iulii anno Domini
                    millesimo quingentesimo quadragesimo quarto.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">
                    <seg type="signature">
                        <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">Nicolaus Olahus episcopus Zagrabiensis
                            etc. manu propria</add>
                    </seg>
                </p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso" xml:id="d.2">
                <head>On the outer side:</head>
                <p xml:id="p.5">Generoso et magnifico domino Leonardo libero baroni a Fels,<note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.3">Leonhard von Vels, nephew of Bernhard von
                        Cles, made a successful military career. He participated in the siege of
                        Vienna in 1529 and became a successor of Wilhelm von Roggendorf as Grand
                        Master of the Court <hi rend="italic">(Oberhofmeister)</hi>, see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Kasza</hi> 2021, 29.</note> supremo magistro curiae ac
                    capitaneo exercitus regiae maiestatis in Hungaria generali etc. domino
                    observandisimo.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
